## Rules

### TEST-001: Arrange-Act-Assert
severity: ERROR
scope: all xUnit/NUnit test methods
rule: All test methods MUST follow the Arrange-Act-Assert pattern with clearly delineated sections. Test methods MUST be named in the format MethodName_Scenario_ExpectedResult.
threshold: min_coverage_pct=80, max_test_file_lines=400
example_correct: |
  [Fact]
  public async Task ProcessOrder_ValidInput_ReturnsSuccess()
  {
      // Arrange
      var order = new Order { ... };
      // Act
      var result = await _sut.ProcessAsync(order);
      // Assert
      Assert.True(result.IsSuccess);
  }
example_incorrect: |
  [Fact]
  public void Test1()
  {
      var r = _sut.Process(new Order());
      Assert.True(r.IsSuccess);
  }

### TEST-002: No Test Interdependencies
severity: ERROR
scope: all xUnit/NUnit test projects
rule: Tests MUST use ITestOutputHelper instead of Console.Write. Tests MUST NOT share static fields or modify class-level state. Each test MUST create its own test doubles via constructor injection.
threshold: min_coverage_pct=80
example_correct: |
  public class OrderTests
  {
      private readonly IOrderService _sut;
      public OrderTests() { _sut = new OrderService(new Mock<IRepo>().Object); }
  }
example_incorrect: |
  public class OrderTests
  {
      private static OrderService _sut = new();  // shared — prohibited
  }
